Benchy is an open source tool for benchmarking section of code after each build.
----
Create a benchmark dll and add a reference to Benchy.Framework.dll.
Write code that sets up and runs the performance critical code.
Mark up the code with [BenchmarkFixture] [SetUp ] [TearDown] [Benchmark] like you would a unit test.
Call Benchy.exe from your build system.
Benchmark results are written to json files which is displayed as a bar graphs.